== Rice ==

Boil a half-full #kettle{}. Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with
@salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @Jasmine Rice{150%grams} and cook for
~{12-13%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{}
and leave to the side until ready to serve.

== Prep ==

While the rice cooks, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Trim and cut the @Green Beans{80%grams} into thirds.

== Mushrooms ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large, deep saucepan with a tight-fitting lid on
high heat.

Once hot, add the @Sliced Mushrooms{80%grams} to the pan. Season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}.

Fry, stirring occasionally, until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

== Bulgogi Beef ==

Once the mushrooms have browned, lower the heat and stir in the garlic and
@Ginger Puree{15%grams}. Fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Add the green beans, @Soy Sauce{15%milliliters} and @Bulgogi Sauce{100%grams},
along with the @Slow Cooked Beef{280%grams} and its juices.

Bring to the boil and simmer on low with the lid on until tender,
~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Ensure the beef is piping hot throughout.

Once tender, remove the lid and gently break up the beef into chunks.

Taste the sauce and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Add a splash of @water{} if you think the sauce is a little thick.

== To Serve ==

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and share between your #bowls{}.

Spoon over the bulgogi beef stew.

Sprinkle over the @Chilli Flakes{1%pinch} (use less if you'd prefer things
milder) to finish.

Enjoy!